<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-02T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="672" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/1285: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Judah</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-02T10:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">June 2,
                                        1928—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:10
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>81. For White. Official decree accepting Chase Bank’s bid for $50,000,000
                            financiering issued last night.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Judah</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
